race.comment: Matt Dale-trained ADOLPHUS (6) led winning a Highway at Rosehill over 1500m and then tackled a 78 there and pulled up with an issue. He's back after 20 days suggesting all is well and the in-form Boudvillain is booked. Beautifully placed and will be hard to beat. DYNAMIC ONE (8) ran a cracking race, winning a 66 at Gundagai over 1800m. Comes back to the mile but expect him to hold the form, and he tumbles in weight. Will hit the line hard. Stablemate MATHRIN (5) surprised the market when winning a 70 at Canberra and had to do it the hard way. That stacks up, and JVO replaces the apprentice. Worth following up, as well. VERMICELLA (12) is a local who's sure to be primed from this contest. Newitt's booking is a lead, and she's won 2/2 third-up. The blinkers go on for the first time.
